.TH dfstab 4 "15 Aug 2008" "SunOS 5.11" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
dfstab \- file containing commands for sharing resources across a network
.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
\fBdfstab\fR resides in directory \fB/etc/dfs\fR and contains commands for
sharing resources across a network. \fBdfstab\fR gives a system
administrator a uniform method of controlling the automatic sharing of local
resources.
.sp
.LP
Each line of the \fBdfstab\fR file consists of a
.BR share (1M)
command.
The \fBdfstab\fR file can be read by the shell to share all resources.
System administrators can also prepare their own shell scripts to execute
particular lines from
.BR dfstab .
.sp
.LP
The contents of \fBdfstab\fR put into effect when the command shown below
is run. See
.BR svcadm (1M).
.sp
.in +2
.nf
/usr/sbin/svcadm enable network/nfs/server
.fi
.in -2

.SH SEE ALSO
.sp
.LP
.BR share (1M),
.BR shareall (1M),
.BR sharemgr (1M),
.BR svcadm (1M)
.SH NOTES
.sp
.LP
Do not modify this file directly. This file is reconstructed and only
maintained for backwards compatibility. Configuration lines could be lost.
.sp
.LP
Use the \fBsharemgr\fR(1M) command for all share management.
